data.value:
You can’t command your mind what to think about or not. But if you’re aware of what’s going on in your mind, and the futility of thoughts, you will eventually stop.
If you do something for the sake of getting it done, that’s doing. If you do something because you like the process, that’s being. When you are engaged in your passion, that’s when being becomes effortless.
Accepting the present moment requires shifting from a state of doing/thinking to being.
The more impatient you are, the more it signifies you’re living in the future.
